[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Java initialization**\n\nI’m reflecting on how nested classes in Java handle native images. The outer class's static fields are separate, and the constructor initialization for Java 13 isn’t particularly relevant here. It’s interesting to think that the outer class might need initialization for the class literal during the native image build process. But wouldn’t runtime initialization ideally prevent that? This is a bit tricky, and I want to make sure my understanding is clear!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03453f408ac58c580169fc82ac73c48190bddd97d6ca36611d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_ILEtbkkg8BMva_Iwq58NNVEVNwS8u6e71oMhG6myqJmMlHwQ8geFYRdcPRx4NL8GMSOQ_rKtMfAzPkfLFVFODGm39GR1hl2LVM4PMASuUPhIVMhAIbWWlCjzUWTvdKWVruFdfUPS3-x3MHBQ6vLBsFg4Gblokwe5npFeiP3EmWgEq7PN7DseFY7XIb6M01AxsfvjiKuJSDdDTE5FwETOl3lHAun87Vgy9XzEqr0VkLbpfMX1izXL7nixJY2T2BJlV60cA5a33H8Dbq9dpyAk_KdsHfeTBJ0N4xZZq-QzJOh_ngS6fRp_rXOEFSkc6cA-rGvmD2Uxws1iIQ2vdetdEweifmfIb3RmWLLAw6vK8xDg2CTSydFLlh_lbhL5QSYVzj3UUum8NOji5bbbjFPcnNzc3AwprU5_BZpJgLHU-BqDzITnjzwzJhFj6vonmULjOdmGOON3jaPpa48rjeuxOqtvuYHDeqxdUgMZ2AaRbHdmepWRFAeaFnGLjTnIX8vJaVIR7jMgIE--xFUGah1dCJrP0ef69RIIlBwkTOr4GZCJTzGEU7cZI4qV7WC059INwcm6_0uzDbwGgpCiFerCw7qfCKzax2WspUJ539IAHkQMfwPn6FJf4i3Ii4zmNprjVy132tPmo7sAD8CQ0dXucHcW-nyAy-oTpXwtidhWaEBoB8PHYs5rLBI5AwWg-HOTfeIYNTrvjIVcpRTCyfLfJSvvDWxvOJosHL4rQIeNQaeB-rq9LCjER_oz1X8Ie_asf2lZCe93SrWMxZHO1W67BfLpujqPoNOIsDBpNocGxYTnll3TXeLjk5yL3F5d0eWSjjUu_XHtB8FVBDv-UBnQU97Fupd0mNI0WmJvLGsRhsc_aw4op4r4foRbWHJoikktkw9FX-COxjIc027cRdjnM1h5I-Wgjk8OIRLTmyqqja4JYL4jBjPjvu46sW3n9WiVcBwsDnnzxvwb3yh3RUm1i5PYlCM8srK6AHIhlKu0wVdEj6Cwdit796LC42YD5itV2IB6ubknzkleH6OAGB_h7zptQQ8MdqzBuFaidmNOLHu9m3_OrWEffzHpmfrlCyVJj4R1TGfF1405QoWHBHfOLx4VBwsYcyYI6SXMWoK19lpIcs80fsySQbS52I00lFmeQCx5jJGJcgj0wz0qRdKQxZnSZSxmNJ0ezmouKG0xXFyEy-UQ9AJU0WJZDwC0R2F2dFwAMvP1Whe38dTJRVYUs4SW1gPQOv